WorkItem.Description:
The jQuery.is function returns a bool according to the documentation, but the jquery.d.ts definition has it returning a JQuery object:

   is(selector: string): JQuery;
   is(func: (index: any) =>any): JQuery;
   is(element: any): JQuery;
   is(obj: JQuery): JQuery;

I think it should be

   is(selector: string): bool;
   is(func: (index: any) =>any): bool;
   is(element: any): bool;
   is(obj: JQuery): bool;

API: http://api.jquery.com/is/
